Sentencas: An air side current collector (ASCC) for a solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) was fabricated and evaluated.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thirty mass%YSZ-LSM, was selected as a candidate material for ASCC.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Its electrical conductivity at 1000 degrees C and its average thermal expansion coefficient between room temperature and 1000 degrees C were 65 S .
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells
Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The gas channel width of ASCC is very important factor, because the current collecting resistance depends on it strongly.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A 1 cm(2) tell was operated with different current collecting length, which corresponded to the width of the gas channel.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We made it clear that the current collecting resistance was very small when the channel width was less than or equal to 3 mm, The SOFC short-stack was built with a 140 cm(2) cell and two ceramic gas separators.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The separator was composed of MgO-MgAl2O4 separate plates, La (Sr) CrO3 current passages and current collectors.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electric power generation test was carried out at 1000 degrees C for 700 h. The cell attained the output power 36 RT at the current 48 A, The voltage loss at the gas separator with a current 45 A was 68 mV, accordingly the electric resistance of the separator was 1.5 m Omega.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electric resistance did not change after a thermal cycle conducted between 1000 degrees C and room temperature.
Titulo: Development of the air side current collector for solid oxide fuel cells
